    • PlayArea

      public PlayArea(Card starterCard, Side side)
      Create a new play area and initialize it with the first PlayArea.CardPlacement.

      The initial card is placed at PlayArea.Position.ORIGIN.

      Parameters:
      starterCard - card for the PlayArea.CardPlacement, same as card in placeAt(Position, Card, Side, boolean)
      side - side for the PlayArea.CardPlacement, same as in placeAt(Position, Card, Side, boolean)
      See Also:
      • placeAt(Position, Card, Side)

    • placeAt

      public PlayArea.CardPlacement placeAt(PlayArea.Position position, Card card, Side side) throws IllegalPlacementException
      Place a card at the specified location.

      To be a valid placement the card must:

      1. touch at least on socket corner (that is, a corner where isSocket() == true)
      2. not touch any corners that are filled in (that is, a corner where isSocket() == false)
      Parameters:
      position - the position where to place the card
      card - the card to be placed
      side - which side to place facing up
      Returns:
      the created PlayArea.CardPlacement
      Throws:
      IllegalPlacementException - when trying to create an illegal placement
      See Also:
      • Corner.isSocket()
